<TITLE> Tangail road crash kills two </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tangail, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)  Two people were killed and 11 others injured when a microbus and a truck collided head-on on the Dhaka-Tangail highway Wednesday, said police. A sand-laden truck rammed into a Tangail-bound microbus coming from the opposite direction at Isail in Mirzapur, around 8am, said Mirzapur police chief Md Jahangir Alam. "An old man and his grandson were killed on the spot," said Alam. The dead were identified as Raham Ali, 75, and his grandson Sajib, 8, of Panchdana village in Mirzapur. They had boarded the bus at Zia International Airport along with a relative who had just arrived from abroad. The injured were admitted to Mirzapur Kumudini Hospital. Drivers of the colliding vehicles managed to flee the scene. bdnews
